Description
---
Regions are procedurally generated and populated. Controls can be used to 
navigate regions. Trainer battles are initiated if the player and another 
trainer come into contact. Wild pokemon encounters have a chance of happening
each step the player takes in tall grass. Pokedex database files will be 
searched for and parsed. Game includes all pokemon in Generations I-III. Written
in C++.

Key
---
%  Border
%  Boulder
^  Tree
C  Poke Center
M  Poke Mart
#  Path
:  Grass
.  Clearing
%  Mountain
^  Forest

@  Player Character
h  Hiker
r  Rival
p  Pacer
w  Wanderer
s  Stationary
n  Random Walker

Controls
---
Up                : 'k' or '8' or KEY_UP
Up-Right          : 'u' or '9'
Right             : 'l' or '6' or KEY_RIGHT
Down-Right        : 'n' or '3'
Down              : 'j' or '2' or KEY_DOWN
Down-Left         : 'b' or '1'
Left              : 'h' or '4' or KEY_LEFT
Up-Left           : 'y' or '7'
Pass Turn         : ' ' or '5' or '.'
Enter Building    : '>'
Exit Building     : '<'
Show Trainer List : 't'
Hide Trainer List : ESC or 't'
Quit Game         : 'Q'
Leave Battle      : ESC
Open Bag          : 'B'
Close Bag         : ESC or 'B'
View Party        : 'p'
Close Party       : ESC or 'p'
Select            : ENTER or '>' or '.'
Back              : ESC or '<' or ','

Switches
---
--numtrainers [int] - The number of trainers that will spawn in each region. 
                      If less than 0, random number of trainers will be spawned. (default)
--seed [int] - The seed that will determine all random events.
